<subsection xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="subsec-extraction-of-roots">
<title>Extraction of roots</title>
<p>
    Suppose <m>z_{0} = r_0\text{e}^{\text{iθ}_{0}}\ </m> is the <m>n^{th}</m> root of a non - zero complex number <m>z = re^{i \theta}</m>, where <m>n \geq 2</m>.
</p>
<p>
    Then, <m>z_{0}^{n} = z</m>, which implies that <m> r_0^{n}\text{e}^{\text{i nθ}_{0}} = re^{i \theta}</m>
</p>
<p>
    <m> \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \Rightarrow r_0^{n} = r</m> &amp; <m> \ n\theta_0 \ = \ \ \theta + 2k\pi, \ \ \ \ k = 0, 1, 2, \cdots (n - 1)</m>.
</p>
<p>
    <m> \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \Rightarrow r_0 = (r)^{\frac{1}{n}} \ </m> &amp; <m> \ \theta_0 \ = \frac{\theta}{n} + \frac{2k\pi}{n}</m>
</p>
<p>
    <m>\therefore, \ \ \ z_{0} = \underline {\underline { (r)^{\frac{1}{n}} \left ( \text{e}^{\text{i}\left(\frac{\theta}{n} + \frac{2k\pi}{n}\right)} \right)}} \ ,</m> which is the <m>n^{th}</m> root of <m>z</m>, where <m>n = 2, 3, \cdots</m> and <m>k = 0, 1, 2, \cdots (n - 1)</m> or we can denote it by <m>C_{k} \ \ \ \text{as :} \ \ C_{k} = \underline {\underline { (r)^{\frac{1}{n}} \left( \text{e}^{\text{i}\left(\frac{\theta}{n} + \frac{2k\pi}{n}\right)} \right)}} \ ,</m> where <m>k = 0, 1, 2, \cdots (n - 1)</m>.
</p>

<example>
    <statement>
        <p>
            Find the square roots of the complex number <m>z = 1 + \sqrt{3}i</m>.
        </p>
    </statement>
    <solution>
        <p>
            <m>z = 1 + \sqrt{3}i</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            Here <m> \ \ r = 2, \theta = \frac{\pi}{3}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            Hence <m>C_{k} = (r)^{\frac{1}{n}} \left( \text{e}^{\text{i}\left(\frac{\theta}{n} + \frac{2k\pi}{n}\right)} \right), n = 2\ , \ k = 0, 1</m>.
        </p>
        <p>
            <m>\ \ \ \ \ \ \ \Rightarrow C_{k} = (2)^{\frac{1}{2}} \left ( \text{e}^{\text{i}\left(\frac{\frac{\pi}{3}}{2} + \frac{2k\pi}{2} \right )} \right )</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            <m>\ \ \ \ \ \ \ \Rightarrow C_{k} = \sqrt{2} \left( \text{e}^{\text{i}\left(\frac{\pi}{6} + k\pi\right)} \right)</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            <m> i.) \ \ \text{If} \ \ k = 0</m>, then <m>C_{0} = \sqrt{2} \left( \text{e}^{\text{i}\frac{\pi}{6}} \right) = \sqrt{2} \left( \cos\frac{\pi}{6} + i\sin\frac{\pi}{6} \right) = \sqrt{2} \left ( \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2} + \frac{i}{2} \right ) = \frac{\sqrt{2}}{2} \left ( \sqrt{3} + i \right ) = \underline {\underline {\frac{\sqrt{6}}{2} + \frac{\sqrt{3i}}{2}}}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            <m> ii.) \ \ \text{If} \ \ k = 1</m>, then <m>C_{1} = \sqrt{2} \left( \text{e}^{\text{i}\left(\frac{\pi}{6} + \pi\right)} \right) = \sqrt{2} \left ( \text{cos}\frac{7\pi}{6} + i\text{sin}\frac{7\pi}{6} \right ) = \sqrt{2} \left( \frac{-\sqrt{3}}{2} - \frac{i}{2} \right) = \frac{-\sqrt{2}}{2} \left( \sqrt{3} + i \right) = \underline {\underline {\frac{-\sqrt{6}}{2} - \frac{\sqrt{3i}}{2}}}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            <m>\therefore \ \ \ \text{The square roots of} \ \ \ 1 + \sqrt{3}i \ \text{are} \ \ \ C_{0} = \frac{\sqrt{6}}{2} + \frac{\sqrt{3}i}{2} \ \ </m> &amp; <m> \ \ C_{1} = \frac{- \sqrt{6}}{2} - \frac{\sqrt{3i}}{2}</m>.
        </p>
    </solution>
</example>

<example>
    <statement>
        <p>
            Find the cube roots of the complex number <m>z = 8i</m>.
        </p>
    </statement>
    <solution>
        <p>
            We have <m>z = 8i</m>. Here <m>r = 8, \theta = \frac{\pi}{2}, n = 3, k = 0, 1, 2</m>.
        </p>
        <p>
            Hence, <m>C_{k} = (r)^{\frac{1}{n}} \left( \text{e}^{\text{i}\left(\frac{\theta}{n} + \frac{2k\pi}{n}\right)} \right)</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            <m>\ \ \ \ \ \ \ \Rightarrow C_{k} = (8)^{\frac{1}{3}} \left( \text{e}^{\text{i}\left(\frac{\frac{\pi}{2}}{3} + \frac{2k\pi}{3}\right)} \right)</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            <m>\ \ \ \ \ \ \ \Rightarrow C_{k} = 2 \left( \text{e}^{\text{i}\left(\frac{\pi}{6} + \frac{2k\pi}{3}\right)} \right)</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            <m>i.) \ \ \text{If} \ \ k = 0</m>, then <m>C_{0} = 2 \left( \text{e}^{\text{i}\frac{\pi}{6}} \right) = 2 \left( \cos\frac{\pi}{6} + i\sin\frac{\pi}{6} \right) = 2 \left( \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2} + \frac{i}{2} \right) = \underline {\underline {\sqrt{3} + i}}\ </m>
        </p>
        <p>
            <m>ii.) \ \ \text{If} \ \ k = 1</m>, then <m>C_{1} = 2 \left( \text{e}^{\text{i}\left(\frac{\pi}{6} + \frac{2\pi}{3}\right)} \right) = 2 \left( \cos\frac{5\pi}{6} + i\sin\frac{5\pi}{6} \right) = 2 \left( -\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2} + \frac{i}{2} \right) = \underline {\underline {- \sqrt{3} + i}}\ </m>
        </p>
        <p>
            <m>iii.) \ \ \text{If} \ \ k = 2</m>, then <m>C_{2} = 2 \left( \text{e}^{\text{i}\left(\frac{\pi}{6} + \frac{4\pi}{3}\right)} \right) = 2 \left( \cos\frac{3\pi}{2} + i\sin\frac{3\pi}{2} \right) = 2(0 + - i) = \underline {\underline {- 2i}}\ </m>
        </p>
        <p>
            <m>\therefore \ \ \ \text{The cube roots of} \ \ 8i \ \text{are} \ \ C_{0} = \sqrt{3} + i, C_{1} = -\sqrt{3} + i</m> &amp; <m> C_{2} = -2i</m>.
        </p>
    </solution>
</example>

<exercises xml:id="exercises-subsec-extraction-of-roots">
    <exercise>
        <statement>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Find the square roots of the complex numbers:
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <m>\ \text{(a)}\ \text{z} = \frac{3i}{-1 - i}</m>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <m>\ \text{(b)}\ \text{z} = \left ( \sqrt{3} - i \right )</m>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Show that <m> \ \text{a)} \ \ \left | \text{e}^{i\theta} \right | = 1 \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \text{b)} \ \ \ \overline {\text{e}^{i\theta}} = \text{e}^{-i\theta} </m>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Using mathematical induction, show that <m> \ \text{e}^{i\theta_{1}} \cdot \text{e}^{i\theta_{2}}. \cdots . \text{e}^{i\theta_{n}} = \text{e}^{i(\theta_{1} + \theta_{2} + \cdots + \theta_{n})} </m> <m>n = 2, 3, \cdots</m>
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </statement>
    </exercise>
</exercises>

